<TITLE> Two die of electrocution during rains </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 1 (bdnews24.com)A mother and son died after being electrocuted on a Lalbagh street amid heavy rains in the capital on Wednesday. Four year-old Shawon was playing in front of his house at Najimuddin Road between downpours, when he received an electric shock after coming into contact with a hanging power cable, said locals. His mother, Mariam Begum, 35, rushed to help him and was also electrocuted, said witnesses. Neighbours rushed the two to Dhaka Medical College Hospital where doctors pronounced them both dead. Mariam's husband Shadat Hossain is a rickshaw-puller. He has another son and two daughters. bdn
